article.headline: Cunningham scores 17 as Oklahoma State rolls
article.linkText: Oklahoma State continues hot streak at home
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. -- Oklahoma State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) moved its home winning streak to 31 against non-conference opponents with an 85-36 victory against Texas-Pan American on Saturday.

The Cowgirls (10-2) outscored UTPA 41-14 in the second half and cruised to a sixth-straight win. Tegan Cunningham led OSU with 17 points. Shaunte' Smith and Andrea Riley each scored 12 with Taylor Hardeman adding 11.

The Lady Broncs (8-8) trailed 44-22 at the break and hit just 5-of-24 second-half shots and totaled 25 turnovers.

Epiphany Smith led UTPA with 15 points.
